{"id": 223723104, "title": "Be wary of extreme abortion access laws | READER COMMENTARY", "text": "The recent denunciation of state Sen. Chris West, and by extension all Republicans, by the former chair of Planned Parenthood of Maryland (\u201cHogan will fall in with his party on abortion if elected,\u201d May 19) for failing to support an extreme abortion access law is misplaced. Senator West, known as a thoughtful legislator for his successful work on juvenile justice reform, is not to be reproached for seeking a middle path on abortion even as the rate of unwed motherhood has exploded from 4% in 1970 to 40% today. Planned Parenthood\u2019s fanaticism is unchanged from a century ago when H.L. Mencken wrote: \u201c\u2026nor is the moral virtuoso much more prepossessing when he takes the devil\u2019s side and howls for license instead of restraint. The birth controllers, for example, often carry on their indelicate crusade with the pious rancor of prohibitionists. In order that women may cease to be ruined for one banal indiscretion, we are now asked to abandon not only the idea of chastity but that of fidelity to contract.\u201d \u2014 George W. Liebmann, Baltimore Add your voice: Respond to this piece or other Sun content by submitting your own letter.", "summary": "Republicans are correct to fear that too-easy access to abortion can have a harmful impact on society.", "url": "https://www.baltimoresun.com/2024/05/26/liberal-abortion-laws/", "image": "https://www.baltimoresun.com/wp-content/uploads/2024/04/Abortion_Arizona_08081_940b10.jpg?w=1024", "video": null, "publish_date": "2024-05-26 14:36:41", "author": "Reader Commentary", "authors": ["Reader Commentary"], "language": "en", "source_country": "US", "sentiment": -0.398}